description: "They" as in my mom 😅👇 In 2019, it was taboo to speak about financial literacy on social media - especially TikTok. When I first started Priceless Tay, our (as in now my team and I) financial literacy platform gained awareness quickly... both highly positive and highly negative. On one side of the room, we had media outlets like Good Morning America call us wanting to feature our financial literacy tips for Gen Z (which we did).  On the other side of the room, we had critics - absolute haters who were a bit older, worked in traditional finance, and did not agree with a young woman (me) speaking about financial literacy on the internet. Needless to say, 5 years later. I'm still here. My team is still here. You're still here. Or if you new, welcome and follow @pricelesstay. Millions around the world are financially thriving, not just survive because we kept serving helpful financial literacy education that was not ever taught in school. #financialliteracy #financialliteracy101 #financialliteracyforbeginners #financialliteracytips #personalfinance #pricelesstay
